headline: USB Q1 Deep Dive: Payments Transformation, Expense Discipline, and Leadership Transition Shape Outlook
summary: Financial services giant U.S. Bancorp (NYSE:USB) reported Q1 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 3.6% year on year to $6.93 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.03 per share was 5.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
